    • Constructor Detail

      • Trigger

        public Trigger(String triggerName,
               String script)
        This constructor does not initialize the fields. It is essential to call init() method in order to make the Trigger work properly. If you want to create a Trigger with customized behavior, it's not necessary to call init() but need to override initInterpreter(Map), startInterpretation(Object, Map, Interpreter, boolean), or activate(Object, Map) method as your need
        Parameters:
        script -

      • activate

        public boolean activate(Object e,
                        Map<String,Object> scriptVars)
        Start this trigger. Variables in scriptVars may be overridden if it has same name as the name of fields of Event class.
        Parameters:
        e - the Event associated with this Trigger
        scriptVars - the temporary local variables
        Returns:
        true if activated; false if on cooldown

      • startInterpretation

        protected void startInterpretation(Object e,
                                   Map<String,Object> scriptVars,
                                   Interpreter interpreter,
                                   boolean sync)
        Start interpreting the code.
        Parameters:
        e - The Event associated with this Trigger
        scriptVars - temporary variables
        interpreter - The Interpreter
        sync - set it true will make this method run in the thread that has called this method. This is useful when this trigger has to cancel an Event; set it to false will let it run in separate thread. This is more efficient if you only need to read data from Event and never interact with it.
